                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <head>407. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to His Special Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BMG1" type="to">Bundy</persName>)<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d407fn1">Source: Kennedy Library, National Security
                        Files, Countries Series, Laos: General, 7/1/62–7/16/62. The memorandum was
                        not signed or initialed by <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>.
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">Bundy</persName> wrote the following note on
                        the source text: “done &amp; understood.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-07-03">July 3, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I do not want any further assistance to go to the Laotian Government unless it is
                    cleared here first.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
